{"word":"ὀπίζομαι","slug":"ὀπίζομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὀπίζομαι</b></el> <el>(ὀπίζομαι,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ὄπις'><el>ὄπις</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a>, <i>to regard with awe and dread</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>vereri, revereri</el>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>:—<a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <el>ὀπιζόμενος</el> <i>a pious man</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>; <el>χάρις ὀπιζομένα</el> <i>pious</i> gratitude, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to care for</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>: —so in <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>Act.</a></a> <el>σώματος ὀπίζων</el> <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}